@startuml DFD_Level2_Notification_Management
!define RECTANGLE class

skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

' External Entities
actor "Pet Owner" as Owner <<External Entity>>
actor "Veterinarian" as Vet <<External Entity>>
database "Firebase FCM" as FCM <<External System>>

' Level 2 Processes for Notification Management (7.0)
rectangle "7.1\nSchedule\nReminders" as ScheduleReminder <<Process>>
rectangle "7.2\nProcess Scheduled\nNotifications" as ProcessScheduled <<Process>>
rectangle "7.3\nSend Push\nNotification" as SendPush <<Process>>
rectangle "7.4\nSend Email\nNotification" as SendEmail <<Process>>
rectangle "7.5\nLog Notification\nDelivery" as LogNotification <<Process>>
rectangle "7.6\nManage User\nPreferences" as ManagePrefs <<Process>>
rectangle "7.7\nHandle Notification\nFailures" as HandleFailures <<Process>>

' Data Stores
database "D1: Users" as D1 <<Data Store>>
database "D6: Appointments" as D6 <<Data Store>>
database "D10: Vaccinations" as D10 <<Data Store>>
database "D14: Notification Queue" as D14 <<Data Store>>
database "D15: Notification Logs" as D15 <<Data Store>>
database "D16: User Preferences" as D16 <<Data Store>>

' Scheduling Flow
D6 --> ScheduleReminder : Appointment Created/Updated\n(24h and 2h before)
D10 --> ScheduleReminder : Vaccination Due Date\n(7 days before)

ScheduleReminder --> D14 : Queue Notification\n(type, user_id, scheduled_time, payload)

' Processing Flow
ProcessScheduled --> D14 : Poll Queue\n(current_time >= scheduled_time)
D14 --> ProcessScheduled : Pending Notifications

ProcessScheduled --> ManagePrefs : Check User Settings
ManagePrefs --> D16 : Get Preferences
D16 --> ManagePrefs : Push/Email/SMS enabled

ManagePrefs --> ProcessScheduled : Preference Status

ProcessScheduled --> SendPush : Send via Push\n(if enabled)
ProcessScheduled --> SendEmail : Send via Email\n(if enabled)

' Push Notification Flow
SendPush --> D1 : Get FCM Token
D1 --> SendPush : User FCM Token

SendPush --> FCM : Notification Payload\n(title, body, data)
FCM --> SendPush : Delivery Status

SendPush --> Owner : Push Notification\n(appointment, vaccination, emergency)
SendPush --> Vet : Appointment Updates

SendPush --> LogNotification : Log Push Delivery

' Email Flow
SendEmail --> D1 : Get Email Address
D1 --> SendEmail : User Email

SendEmail --> Owner : Email Notification
SendEmail --> Vet : Email Alerts

SendEmail --> LogNotification : Log Email Delivery

' Logging Flow
LogNotification --> D15 : Store Log\n(user_id, type, status, timestamp)
LogNotification --> HandleFailures : Delivery Status

' Failure Handling
HandleFailures --> D15 : Log Failure Reason
HandleFailures --> D14 : Retry Queue\n(max 3 attempts)
HandleFailures --> ProcessScheduled : Retry Notification

' Preference Management
Owner --> ManagePrefs : Update Preferences\n(push/email/sms on/off)
ManagePrefs --> D16 : Store Preferences
ManagePrefs --> Owner : Preferences Saved

note right of ScheduleReminder
  Level 2 DFD: Notification Management (7.0)
  
  Sub-processes:
  7.1 - Reminder scheduling (appointments, vaccinations)
  7.2 - Scheduled notification processing
  7.3 - Push notification via Firebase FCM
  7.4 - Email notification sending
  7.5 - Delivery logging
  7.6 - User preference management
  7.7 - Retry logic for failures
  
  Notification Types:
  - Appointment reminders (24-hour and 2-hour intervals)
  - Vaccination reminders (7 days before due date)
  - Emergency alerts from chatbot (urgent keywords detected)
  - Appointment confirmations/cancellations
  - Medication adherence reminders
  - Lost pet alerts (future)
  
  Delivery Channels:
  - Firebase Cloud Messaging (Push)
  - Email (SMTP)
  - SMS (optional, future)
end note

note bottom of D14
  Notification Queue stores:
  - queue_id, user_id, type
  - scheduled_time, payload
  - status (pending/sent/failed)
  - retry_count, created_at
end note

note bottom of D15
  Notification Logs stores:
  - log_id, user_id, type
  - sent_at, delivery_status
  - channel (push/email/sms)
  - error_message (if failed)
end note

note bottom of D16
  User Preferences stores:
  - user_id, push_enabled
  - email_enabled, sms_enabled
  - appointment_reminders
  - vaccination_alerts
  - emergency_alerts
end note

@enduml
